                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" xml:id="abstract1168-1">In hagiography: <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1167">Bassus</persName> and his twin sister Suzanna 
                        were twin children of a Zoroastrian governor. They were informed about Christianity by a
                        Christian slave. They were baptized by an ascetic named <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1342">Longinus</persName>. They were killed by
                        their father. A martyr named <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1229">Stephen</persName> is also commemorated with them.</note>
